Murder cops have launched an investigation after a man was stabbed to death inside a pub in west London. Police rushed to the venue on Uxbridge Road, Ealing, just before midnight. The victim, believed to be in his 50s, was pronounced dead at the scene. Scotland Yard said detectives were looking for witnesses as they widen a probe into the shocking attack. No arrests have been made yet at what the force said was an ‘early stage’ of the investigation. The man’s family have been informed and will be supported by specialist officers. Witnesses are urged to contact police on 101 or call Crimestoppers if they wish to remain anonymous. This is a breaking news story, more to follow soon… Check back shortly for further updates. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check our news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.